The paper discusses proximity searching and best match in large and high-dimensional data sets, which are common problems in data structures (cs.DS), information retrieval (cs.IR), machine learning (cs.LG), databases (cs.DB), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of ultrametric topology and hierarchical structures also suggests a focus on data organization and optimization, which are relevant to these sub-categories.
